-- DEPENDENCIES --

If you want to use SQLite as your chat backend, you need to 
have php5_sqllite installed on your system - refer to your
distributions documentation for how to do this


-- INSTALLATION --

1. Copy the bottom_bar folder and contents to the "mod" directory 
of your ELGG installation

2. IMPORTANT: Make sure that you set the "bottom_bar/data" folder 
to be writable by the web server user
   e.g. 
	chown www-data:www-data bottom_bar/data
	chmod 755 bottom_bar/data

3. Go to the tools administration page on ELGG and enable the 
bottom_bar plugin.

4. Once enabled, update the settings for the plugin as you see fit.

5. Enjoy! :)


-- INTERNET RADIO / PODCAST --

To get this feature to work, you need to either host an MP3 on your
server, or know the address of an icecast (not shoutcast) server.

e.g. - http://scfire-ntc-aa07.stream.aol.com:80/stream/1003

Hint - If you are looking for streams to test with, try Digitally 
Imported - http://www.di.fm - their streams are known to work with 
this player
